9 (12) “Qualified withdrawal” means a withdrawal made as prescribed under ORS 178.355 and
10 made:
11 (a) From an account to pay the qualified higher education expenses of the designated benefici-
12 ary;
13 (b) As the result of the death or disability of the designated beneficiary;
14 (c) As the result of a scholarship, allowance or payment described in section 135(d)(1)(A), (B)
15 or (C) of the Internal Revenue Code that is received by the designated beneficiary, but only to the
16 extent of the amount of the scholarship, allowance or payment; or
17 (d) As a rollover or change in the designated beneficiary described in ORS 178.350.
18 SECTION 2. ORS 178.375 is amended to read:
19 178.375. As used in this section and ORS 178.380 and 178.385:
20 (1) “ABLE account” means an account established by an eligible individual, owned by the eli-
