33 SECTION 3. ORS 238A.005 is amended to read:
34 238A.005. For the purposes of this chapter:
35 (1) “Active member” means a member of the pension program or the individual account program
36 of the Oregon Public Service Retirement Plan who is actively employed in a qualifying position.
37 (2) “Actuarial equivalent” means a payment or series of payments having the same value as the
38 payment or series of payments replaced, computed on the basis of interest rate and mortality as-
39 sumptions adopted by the board.
40 (3) “Board” means the Public Employees Retirement Board.
41 (4) “Eligible employee” means a person who performs services for a participating public em-
42 ployer, including persons considered employees of a participating public employer under 26 U.S.C.
43 3121(d)(2), as in effect on January 1, [2024] 2026, and elected officials other than judges. “Eligible
44 employee” does not include:
45 (a) Persons engaged as independent contractors;
[2]

HB 4015
1 (b) Aliens working under a training or educational visa;
2 (c) Persons provided sheltered employment or make-work by a public employer;
3 (d) Persons categorized by a participating public employer as student employees;
4 (e) Any person who is in custody in a state institution;
5 (f) Employees of foreign trade offices of the Oregon Business Development Department who live
6 and perform services in foreign countries under the provisions of ORS 285A.075 (1)(g);
7 (g) An employee actively participating in an alternative retirement program established under
8 ORS 353.250 or an optional retirement plan established under ORS 341.551;
9 (h) Employees of a public university listed in ORS 352.002 who are actively participating in an
10 optional retirement plan offered under ORS 243.815;
11 (i) Persons employed in positions classified as post-doctoral scholar positions by a public uni-
12 versity listed in ORS 352.002, or by the Oregon Health and Science University, under ORS 350.370;
13 (j) Any employee who belongs to a class of employees that was not eligible on August 28, 2003,
14 for membership in the system under the provisions of ORS chapter 238 or other law;
15 (k) Any person who belongs to a class of employees who are not eligible to become members
16 of the Oregon Public Service Retirement Plan under the provisions of ORS 238A.070 (2);
17 (L) Any person who is retired under ORS 238A.100 to 238A.250 or ORS chapter 238 and who
18 continues to receive retirement benefits while employed; and
19 (m) Judges.
20 (5) “Firefighter” means:
21 (a) A person employed by a local government, as defined in ORS 174.116, whose primary job
22 duties include the fighting of fires;
23 (b) The State Fire Marshal, chief deputy state fire marshals and deputy state fire marshals;
24 (c) An employee of the State Fire Marshal whose primary duties include fire investigation, fire
25 prevention, fire safety, fire control or fire suppression;
26 (d) An employee of the State Forestry Department who is certified by the State Forester as a
27 professional wildland firefighter and whose primary duties include the abatement of uncontrolled
28 fires as described in ORS 477.064; and
29 (e) An employee of the Oregon Military Department whose primary duties include fighting
30 structural, aircraft, wildland or other fires.
31 (6) “Fund” means the Public Employees Retirement Fund.
32 (7)(a) “Hour of service” means:
33 (A) An hour for which an eligible employee is directly or indirectly paid or entitled to payment
34 by a participating public employer for performance of duties in a qualifying position; and
35 (B) An hour of vacation, holiday, illness, incapacity, jury duty, military duty or authorized leave
36 during which an employee does not perform duties but for which the employee is directly or indi-
37 rectly paid or entitled to payment by a participating public employer for services in a qualifying
38 position, as long as the hour is within the number of hours regularly scheduled for the performance
39 of duties during the period of vacation, holiday, illness, incapacity, jury duty, military duty or au-
40 thorized leave.
41 (b) “Hour of service” does not include any hour for which payment is made or due under a plan
42 maintained solely for the purpose of complying with applicable unemployment compensation laws.
43 (8) “Inactive member” means a member of the pension program or the individual account pro-
44 gram of the Oregon Public Service Retirement Plan whose membership has not been terminated, who
45 is not a retired member and who is not employed in a qualifying position.
