15 SECTION 5. ORS 238A.125 is amended to read:
16 238A.125. (1) Upon retiring at normal retirement age, a vested pension program member shall
17 be paid an annual pension for the life of the member as follows:
18 (a) For service as a police officer or firefighter, 1.8 percent of final average salary multiplied
19 by the number of years of retirement credit attributable to service as a police officer or firefighter.
20 (b) For service as other than a police officer or firefighter, 1.5 percent of final average salary
21 multiplied by the number of years of retirement credit attributable to service as other than a police
22 officer or firefighter.
23 (2) Notwithstanding any provision of ORS 238A.100 to 238A.250, the annual benefit payable to
24 a member under the pension program and under any other tax-qualified defined benefit plan main-
25 tained by the participating public employer may not exceed the applicable limitations set forth in
26 26 U.S.C. 415(b), as in effect on December 31, [2023] 2025. The Public Employees Retirement Board
27 shall adopt rules for the administration of this limitation, including adjustments in the annual dollar
28 limitation to reflect cost-of-living adjustments authorized by the Internal Revenue Service.
29 (3) The board shall make no actuarial adjustment in a member’s pension calculated under this
30 section by reason of the member’s retirement after normal retirement age.
31 SECTION 6. ORS 238A.125, as amended by section 3, chapter 101, Oregon Laws 2024, is
