8 vices, and who subsequently returns to employment with a participating public employer with
9 reemployment rights under federal law, is entitled to accrue retirement credit, credit toward the
10 probationary period required by ORS 238A.100 and credit toward the vesting requirements of ORS
11 238A.115 under rules adopted by the Public Employees Retirement Board pursuant to subsection (2)
12 of this section.
13 (2) The board shall adopt rules establishing benefits and service credit for any period of service
14 in the uniformed services by an employee described in subsection (1) of this section. For the purpose
15 of adopting rules under this subsection, the board shall consider and take into account all federal
16 law relating to benefits and service credit for any period of service in the uniformed services, in-
17 cluding 26 U.S.C. 414(u), as in effect on December 31, [2023] 2025. Benefits and service credit under
18 rules adopted by the board pursuant to this subsection may not exceed benefits and service credit
19 required under federal law for periods of service in the uniformed services.
