45 (C) Basis of the property of the taxpayer, excluding amounts subject to the election under sec-
[17]

HB 4015
1 tion 108(b)(5) of the Internal Revenue Code.
2 (D) Passive activity loss carryover.
3 (c) Excluding amounts subject to the election in section 108(b)(5) of the Internal Revenue Code:
4 (A) Any Oregon net operating loss of an individual or corporate taxpayer, including a net op-
5 erating loss carryover to the taxpayer, shall be reduced by the amount of discharged indebtedness.
6 (B) Any net capital loss for the taxable year of the discharge, and any capital loss carryover to
7 the taxable year, shall be reduced by the amount of discharged indebtedness minus the total amount
8 taken into account under subparagraph (A) of this paragraph.
9 (C) The basis of the property of the taxpayer shall be reduced by the amount of discharged
10 indebtedness minus the total amount taken into account under subparagraphs (A) and (B) of this
11 paragraph.
12 (D) The passive activity loss carryover under section 469(b) of the Internal Revenue Code from
13 the taxable year of the discharge shall be reduced by the amount of discharged indebtedness minus
14 the total amount taken into account under subparagraphs (A), (B) and (C) of this paragraph.
