28 shall apply and follow the administrative and judicial interpretations of the federal income tax law.
29 When a provision of the federal income tax law is the subject of conflicting opinions by two or more
30 federal courts, the department shall follow the rule observed by the United States Commissioner of
31 Internal Revenue until the conflict is resolved. Nothing contained in this section limits the right
32 or duty of the department to audit the return of any taxpayer or to determine any fact relating to
33 the tax liability of any taxpayer.
34 (4) When portions of the Internal Revenue Code incorporated by reference as provided in sub-
35 section (2) of this section refer to rules or regulations prescribed by the Secretary of the Treasury,
36 then such rules or regulations shall be regarded as rules adopted by the department under and in
37 accordance with the provisions of this chapter, whenever they are prescribed or amended.
38 (5)(a) When portions of the Internal Revenue Code incorporated by reference as provided in
39 subsection (2) of this section are later corrected by an Act or a Title within an Act of the United
40 States Congress designated as an Act or Title making technical corrections, then notwithstanding
41 the date that the Act or Title becomes law, those portions of the Internal Revenue Code, as so
42 corrected, shall be the portions of the Internal Revenue Code incorporated by reference as provided
43 in subsection (2) of this section and shall take effect, unless otherwise indicated by the Act or Title
44 (in which case the provisions shall take effect as indicated in the Act or Title), as if originally in-
45 cluded in the provisions of the Act being technically corrected. If, on account of this subsection, any
[18]

HB 4015
1 adjustment is required to an Oregon return that would otherwise be prevented by operation of law
2 or rule, the adjustment shall be made, notwithstanding any law or rule to the contrary, in the
3 manner provided under ORS 314.135.
