34 SECTION 28. ORS 317A.100, as amended by section 6, chapter 502, Oregon Laws 2025, is
35 amended to read:
36 317A.100. As used in ORS 317A.100 to 317A.158:
37 (1)(a) “Commercial activity” means:
38 (A) The total amount realized by a person, arising from transactions and activity in the regular
39 course of the person’s trade or business, without deduction for expenses incurred by the trade or
40 business;
41 (B) If received by a financial institution:
42 (i) If the reporting person for a financial institution is a holding company, all items of income
43 reported on the FR Y-9 filed by the holding company;
44 (ii) If the reporting person for a financial institution is a bank organization, all items of income
45 reported on the call report filed by the bank organization; and
[28]

HB 4015
1 (iii) If the reporting person for a financial institution is a nonbank financial organization, all
2 items of income reported in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles; and
3 (C)(i) If received by an insurer, as reported on the statement of premiums accompanying the
4 annual statement required under ORS 731.574 to be filed with the Director of the Department of
5 Consumer and Business Services, all gross direct life insurance premiums, gross direct accident and
6 health insurance premiums and gross direct property and casualty insurance premiums; and
7 (ii) The gross amount of surplus lines premiums received on Oregon home state risks as shown
8 in the report required by ORS 735.465.
9 (b) “Commercial activity” does not include:
10 (A) Interest income except:
11 (i) Interest on credit sales; or
12 (ii) Interest income, including service charges, received by financial institutions;
13 (B) Receipts from the sale, exchange or other disposition of an asset described in section 1221
14 or 1231 of the Internal Revenue Code, without regard to the length of time the person held the asset;
15 (C) If received by an insurer, federally reinsured premiums or income from transactions between
16 a reciprocal insurer and its attorney in fact operating under ORS 731.142;
17 (D) Receipts from hedging transactions, to the extent that the transactions are entered into
18 primarily to protect a financial position, including transactions intended to manage the risk of ex-
19 posure to foreign currency fluctuations that affect assets, liabilities, profits, losses, equity or in-
20 vestments in foreign operations, risk of exposure to interest rate fluctuations or risk of commodity
21 price fluctuations;
22 (E) Proceeds received attributable to the repayment, maturity or redemption of the principal of
23 a loan, bond, mutual fund, certificate of deposit or marketable instrument;
24 (F) The principal amount received under a repurchase agreement or on account of any trans-
25 action properly characterized as a loan to the person;
26 (G) Contributions received by a trust, plan or other arrangement, any of which is described in
27 section 501(a) of the Internal Revenue Code, or to which title 26, subtitle A, chapter 1, subchapter
28 (D) of the Internal Revenue Code applies;
29 (H) Compensation, whether current or deferred, and whether in cash or in kind, received or to
30 be received by an employee, a former employee or the employee’s legal successor for services ren-
31 dered to or for an employer, including reimbursements received by or for an individual for medical
32 or education expenses, health insurance premiums or employee expenses or on account of a de-
33 pendent care spending account, legal services plan, any cafeteria plan described in section 125 of
34 the Internal Revenue Code or any similar employee reimbursement;
35 (I) Proceeds received from the issuance of the taxpayer’s own stock, options, warrants, puts or
