16 (19)(a) “Unitary business” means a business enterprise in which there exists directly or indi-
17 rectly between the members or parts of the enterprise a sharing or exchange of value as demon-
18 strated by:
19 (A) Centralized management or a common executive force;
20 (B) Centralized administrative services or functions resulting in economies of scale; or
21 (C) Flow of goods, capital resources or services demonstrating functional integration.
22 (b) “Unitary business” may include a business enterprise the activities of which:
23 (A) Are in the same general line of business, such as manufacturing, wholesaling or retailing;
24 or
25 (B) Constitute steps in a vertically integrated process, such as the steps involved in the pro-
26 duction of natural resources, which might include exploration, mining, refining and marketing.
27 (20) “Unitary group” means a group of persons with more than 50 percent common ownership,
28 either direct or indirect, that is engaged in business activities that constitute a unitary business.
29 (21) “Wholesaler” means a person primarily doing business by merchant distribution of tangible
30 personal property to retailers or to other wholesalers.
